editorialSummary.text: Performing & visual arts complex with a small venue for dance & theater events, plus studio rentals.

originalText.text: This is a wonderful, welcoming, creative and versatile space. The staff is super friendly and flexible when possible, and I always look forward to renting a room and working here. Curt is especially kind, as well as Sherlene - but really everyone! I particularly love the warm kitchen area with all the plants, where you can have a cup of tea and enjoy the view. I would definitely recommend Alchemical to anyone looking for a versatile space to create, connect, etc.

originalText.text:
I've been trying to book a space for my performance with this studio, and I must say, it has been an incredibly frustrating experience.

On three separate occasions over the past three weeks, I had to reach out to the office to get him to contact me back. Even when he finally got back to me, it was clear that he had no recollection of our previous conversations. He frequently forgot crucial details of our arrangements, forcing me to repeat myself.

Despite his initial request to text and call his personal number, it's become evident that this method of communication is unreliable. The urgency of my performance requires timely responses, but I've often been met with silence for days.

What's most disappointing is the lack of professionalism in our interactions. During our last call, he rudely dismissed my concerns and suggested that I find another venue before hanging up on me. It's incredibly disheartening to see such disregard for potential clients. I was on the final step of booking at this point.

I want to believe that this behavior is truly "out of character," as I've been told by others at the studio. However, the consistency of these issues is concerning.

Booking a performance space should be a smooth and efficient process, but my experience with this studio has been anything but. I hope they take this feedback as an opportunity for improvement.
